    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=The current date is: {{ $json.date }}\nLeap year status: {{ $json.leapyear }}\n\nAnalyze the following email exchange in Czech/Slovak to determine which rezervation or rezervations the user would like to cancel. If there is a single rezervation they would like to cancel in the most recent user email, output the time in such a way that it matches this format - 'time: 1970-01-01TXX:XX:XX.000Z, date: YYYY-MM-DD' where X refers to a digit in the time. If there are many rezervations they want to cancel in the most recent user email, use the format specified but separate each rezervation with a comma. If the user responds by referencing a rezervation with incomplete information, try to figure out which rezervation they meant and output that. If you are sure that in the most recent user mail the user has specified a rezervation that wasn't mentioned in the admin response or if the time the user mentioned is off by more than 20 minutes or if the date the user mentions is off by a day or more, output 'couldn't identify rezervation'. Remember when a user uses '.' after a number, its usually refering to a date, not a time. Pay attention to plural and singular in the user responses about rezervations. If singular, assume they only want to cancel one reservation. Here is the email correspondence: {{ $('When Executed by Another Workflow').item.json.contents }}\n\n\n",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "type": "HumanMessagePromptTemplate",
              "message": "="
            }
          ]
        },
